@title Cardinal House Presale contract
 @dev Contract responsible for the Cardinal House presale mechanisms

@dev Once the Cardinal Token contract is deployed, this function is used to set a reference to that token in this contract.
 @param CardinalTokenAddress address of the Cardinal Token.

@dev Gets the amount of Cardinal Tokens the sender owns.
 @return the Cardinal Token balance of the sender

@dev Returns the contract address
 @return contract address

@dev Returns the Cardinal Token address
 @return Cardinal Token contract address

documentation.text: @dev Allows a user to pay Matic for Cardinal Tokens. Conversion rate is 1 Matic to MaticToCRNLRate Cardinal Tokens (CRNL) where MaticToCRNLRate is the variable defined in the contract.

@dev Only owner function to change the presale Cardinal Token purchase cap per user.
 @param newPurchaseCap the new Cardinal Token purchase cap in CRNL (NOT Matic). Use the conversion rate to figure out how many Cardinal Tokens to set here.

@dev Only owner function to change the conversion rate for Matic to Cardinal Token.
 @param newConversionRate the new Matic to Cardinal Token conversion rate.

@dev Only owner function to withdraw the Matic from this contract.
 @param amount the amount of Matic to withdraw from the pre-sale contract.

@dev Gets the amount of Matic that the contract has.
 @return the amount of Matic the contract has.

@dev Gets the Cardinal Token balance of the contract.
 @return the amount of Cardinal Tokens the contract has.

natspec.details: Contract responsible for the Cardinal House presale mechanisms

changeCardinalTokenPurchaseCap(uint256).details: Only owner function to change the presale Cardinal Token purchase cap per user.

params.newPurchaseCap: the new Cardinal Token purchase cap in CRNL (NOT Matic). Use the conversion rate to figure out how many Cardinal Tokens to set here.

changeMaticToCardinalTokenRate(uint256).details: Only owner function to change the conversion rate for Matic to Cardinal Token.

params.newConversionRate: the new Matic to Cardinal Token conversion rate.

getContractMatic().details: Gets the amount of Matic that the contract has.

returns._0: the amount of Matic the contract has.

getContractTokens().details: Gets the Cardinal Token balance of the contract.

returns._0: the amount of Cardinal Tokens the contract has.

getUserBalance().details: Gets the amount of Cardinal Tokens the sender owns.

returns._0: the Cardinal Token balance of the sender

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

purchaseCardinalTokens().details: Allows a user to pay Matic for Cardinal Tokens. Conversion rate is 1 Matic to MaticToCRNLRate Cardinal Tokens (CRNL) where MaticToCRNLRate is the variable defined in the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setToken(address).details: Once the Cardinal Token contract is deployed, this function is used to set a reference to that token in this contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawMatic(uint256).details: Only owner function to withdraw the Matic from this contract.

params.amount: the amount of Matic to withdraw from the pre-sale contract.
